<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1435,1986,2011]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,356]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1986,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Crown of head medially longer than next to eyes, face convex in lateral view. Pronotum transversely rugose. Male pygofer bearing lobe produced caudoventrally into acute process, anal collar appendage well developed, subgenital plates boat-shaped in lateral view, with row of stout setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
